==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''accumulatio''; compare French ''accumulation''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-accumulation.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|eɪʃǝn}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The act of [[accumulating]], the state of being [[accumulated]], or that which is [[accumulated]]; as, an ''accumulation'' of earth, of sand, of evils, of wealth, of honors.
# {{legal}} The [[concurrence]] of several titles to the same proof.
# {{accounting}} The continuous growth of [[capital]] by [[retention]] of [[interest]] or [[savings]].
# (investment) The action of experienced investors buying an asset from inexperienced investors when the price of the asset is low.

====Synonyms====
